<% provide(:title, "Help") %>

<h1 class="fw-light">Help Center</h1>

<div class="text-muted">

  <p>
    Welcome to <strong>StudyMates</strong> — a collaborative platform designed to help you connect with like-minded professionals,
    join discussions, and grow through shared learning experiences.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h5>Getting Started</h5>
  <ul>
    <li>Create your account and complete your profile with a profile picture and bio</li>
    <li>Explore users and connect with study partners based on your interests</li>
    <li>Join or create rooms to participate in focused discussions</li>
    <li>Use the search feature to find rooms by topic or name if your feed is empty</li>
    <li>Start conversations by sending messages inside rooms</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h5>Features Overview</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Rooms:</strong> Join topic-based spaces for discussions and collaboration</li>
    <li><strong>Feed:</strong> Personalized stream of rooms from people you follow and participate in</li>
    <li><strong>Following System:</strong> Follow other users to stay updated with their activity</li>
    <li><strong>Messaging:</strong> Share ideas, resources, and files within rooms</li>
    <li><strong>Search:</strong> Quickly find rooms or topics using keywords</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h5>Common Questions</h5>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p class="m-0"><strong>How do I connect with others?</strong></p>
      <small>Visit user profiles and follow them to stay updated with their activity and rooms.</small>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p class="m-0"><strong>How do I join a room?</strong></p>
      <small>Click on any room and start participating — you will automatically be added as a participant when you interact.</small>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p class="m-0"><strong>How do I update my profile?</strong></p>
      <small>Go to your profile page and click edit to update your details, including your avatar.</small>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p class="m-0"><strong>What if I don't see any content in my feed?</strong></p>
      <small>Your feed depends on your activity. Try following users or joining rooms, or use search to explore topics.</small>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p class="m-0"><strong>Having technical issues?</strong></p>
      <small>Try refreshing the page, clearing your browser cache, or logging out and back in. If the issue persists, contact support.</small>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h5>Email Not Received or Account Not Activated?</h5>

  <p>
    If you signed up or requested a password reset but did not receive an email,
    please read the information below carefully.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Check your <strong>Spam</strong>, <strong>Promotions</strong>, or <strong>Updates</strong> folder</li>
    <li>Wait a few minutes, as email delivery may be delayed</li>
    <li>Make sure the email address entered is correct</li>
    <li>Try requesting the email again from the relevant page</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h6>Important Notice</h6>

  <p>
    <strong>StudyMates is currently running on a free-tier deployment (Render + external email service).</strong>
  </p>

  <p>
    Because of this, email delivery (account activation and password reset) may occasionally be delayed or fail due to
    external service limitations or rate restrictions.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you are unable to verify your account or reset your password, you can still explore the application using the
    <strong>mock/demo users</strong> provided below.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Email:</strong> jack@example.com</li>
    <li><strong>Password:</strong> jack123</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    These demo accounts allow you to test all core features including rooms, messaging, and user interactions.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h6>Why this happens</h6>

  <ul>
    <li>Email services (SMTP providers) may throttle free-tier traffic</li>
    <li>Background jobs (Sidekiq) may be limited on free hosting plans</li>
    <li>External services can temporarily block automated emails</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <p>
    We are actively working on improving email reliability. Thank you for your understanding.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h5>Best Practices</h5>
  <ul>
    <li>Be respectful and constructive in discussions</li>
    <li>Join rooms relevant to your interests for better recommendations</li>
    <li>Follow active users to improve your feed quality</li>
    <li>Use clear room names and descriptions when creating content</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <p>
    Need more help? Reach out anytime via the
    <%= link_to "Contact page", contact_path, class: "text-dark" %>.
  </p>

</div>